    "Our exploration involves two main experiments.",
    "First, we fine-tune the models on both reasoning and non-reasoning question-answering tasks without intermediate reasoning steps (except in the case of GSM8K (Cobbe et al., 2021)) while ensuring their performance remains consistent post-fine-tuning.",
    "Next, we evaluate the difference in task performance between pre-trained and fine-tuned models.",
    "We investigate how fine-tuning LLMs on various datasets -such as mathematical, common-sense reasoning, and medical datasets -affects the accu-racy of their CoT reasoning abilities.",
    "Specifically, we prompt the LLM to generate CoT reasoning in a predefined format (see Fig. 1)."
